{"title_page": "Miss International 1999", "text_new": "{{Infobox beauty pageant\n| winner = '''[[Paulina G\u00e1lvez (Miss International)|Paulina G\u00e1lvez]]'''<ref name=straits/>\n| represented = '''{{flag|Colombia}}'''\n| date = December 14, 1999<ref name=straits/>\n| presenters = [[Masumi Okada]], Mari Christine\n| venue = U-Port Hall, [[Tokyo]], [[Japan]]<ref name=straits/>\n| broadcaster = [[TV Tokyo]]\n| entrants = 51<ref name=tiempo/>\n| placements = 15\n| photogenic = [[Paulina G\u00e1lvez (Miss International)|Paulina G\u00e1lvez]] <br> {{flag|Colombia}}<ref name=tiempo/>\n| congeniality = Miyuki Hill <br> {{flag|Northern Marianas}}<ref name=straits/>\n| debuts = [[Egypt]], [[Palau]]\n| withdraws = [[Australia]], [[Cura\u00e7ao]], [[Honduras]], [[Netherlands|Holland]], [[Paraguay]], [[Peru]]\n| returns = [[Brazil]], [[C\u00f4te d'Ivoire]], [[Guam]], [[Guatemala]], [[Lebanon]], [[Malaysia]], [[Malta]], [[Nicaragua]], [[Russia]], [[Ukraine]], [[Uruguay]]\n| before = [[Miss International 1998|1998]]\n| next = [[Miss International 2000|2000]]\n}}\n\n'''Miss International 1999''', the 39th [[Miss International]] pageant, was held on 14 December 1999 at the U-Port Hall in [[Tokyo]], [[Japan]] and hosted by [[Masumi Okada]] and Mari Christine. [[Paulina G\u00e1lvez (Miss International)|Paulina G\u00e1lvez]] of [[Colombia]] was crowned at the end of the event, becoming the second titleholder from her country to win Miss International.\n\n==Results==\n\n===Placements===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n|-\n! Final results\n! Contestant\n|-\n| '''Miss International 1999'''\n|\n* '''{{flag|Colombia}}''' - '''[[Paulina G\u00e1lvez (Miss International)|Paulina G\u00e1lvez]]'''\n|-\n| '''1st runner-up'''\n|\n* '''{{flag|Spain}}''' - Carmen Fern\u00e1ndez\n|-\n| '''2nd runner-up'''\n|\n* '''{{flag|Finland}}''' - Saija Palin\n|-\n| '''Semi-finalists'''\n|\n* '''{{flag|Brazil}}''' - Alessandra do Nascimento\n* '''{{flag|Cura\u00e7ao}}''' - Pamela 