nd of the event, becoming the second titleholder from her country to win Miss International.\n\n==Results==\n\n===Placements===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n|-\n! Final results\n! Contestant\n|-\n| '''Miss International 1999'''\n|\n* '''{{flag|Colombia}}''' - '''[[Paulina G\u00e1lvez (Miss International)|Paulina G\u00e1lvez]]'''\n|-\n| '''1st runner-up'''\n|\n* '''{{flag|Spain}}''' - Carmen Fern\u00e1ndez\n|-\n| '''2nd runner-up'''\n|\n* '''{{flag|Finland}}''' - Saija Palin\n|-\n| '''Semi-finalists'''\n|\n* '''{{flag|Brazil}}''' - Alessandra do Nascimento\n* '''{{flag|Cura\u00e7ao}}''' - Pamela Winkel\n* '''{{flag|Cyprus}}''' - Afroditi Pericleous\n* '''{{flag|Czech Republic}}''' - S\u00e1rka Sikorova\n* '''{{flag|Dominican Republic}}''' - Patsi Arias\n* '''{{flag|Japan|1999}}''' - Kana Onoda\n* '''{{flag|Nicaragua}}''' - Claudia Alaniz\n* '''{{flag|Poland}}''' - Adrianna Gerczew\n* '''{{flag|Russia}}''' - Maria Tchebotkevitch\n* '''{{flag|Senegal}}''' - A\u00efcha Faye\n* '''{{flag|Uruguay}}''' - Daniela Abasolo\n* '''{{flag|Venezuela|1954}}''' - [[Andre\u00edna Llamozas]]\n|}\n\n==Contestants==\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n* '''{{flag|Argentina}}''' - Elizabeth Contrard\n* '''{{flag|Aruba}}''' - Cindy Vanessa Cam Lin Martinus\n* '''{{flag|Bolivia}}''' - Natalia Arteaga\n* '''{{flag|Brazil}}''' - Alessandra do Nascimento\n* {{flagicon|Britain}} '''[[United Kingdom|Britain]]''' - Janeth Kehinde Ayuba\n* '''{{flag|Colombia}}''' - [[Paulina G\u00e1lvez (Miss International)|Paulina G\u00e1lvez]]\n* '''{{flag|C\u00f4te d'Ivoire}}''' - Madaussou Kamara\n* '''{{flag|Cura\u00e7ao}}''' - Pamela Winkel\n* '''{{flag|Cyprus}}''' - Afroditi Pericleous\n* '''{{flag|Czech Republic}}''' - S\u00e1rka Sikorov\u00e1\n* '''{{flag|Dominican Republic}}''' - Patsi Arias\n* '''{{flag|Egypt}}''' - Engy Mohammed Abdalla\n* '''{{flag|Finland}}''' - Saija Palin\n* '''{{flag|France}}''' - C\u00e9line Cheuva\n* '''{{flag|Germany}}''' - Tania Freuderberg\n* '''{{flag